trans-unit.source: A page can be defined by using markup, markup and code-behind, or code.
trans-unit.target: En side kan defineres ved å bruke markup, markup og bakenforliggende kode eller kode.

trans-unit.source: A page is the preferred way to package content for navigation, for the following reasons: - It is easy to define, reuse, and manage.
trans-unit.target: En side er den foretrukne måten å pakkens innhold for navigasjon av følgende årsaker:-Det er enkelt å definere gjenbruk og administrere.

trans-unit.source: - It can access and use the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> that navigated to it.
trans-unit.target: -Det kan få tilgang til og bruke <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>som mulig å navigere til det.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.source: - It can alter the title, width, height, and navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] of its host window (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowTitle%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowWidth%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowHeight%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.ShowsNavigationUI%2A>).
trans-unit.target: -Det kan endre tittelen, bredden, høyden og navigasjon [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] av vinduet vert (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowTitle%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowWidth%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowHeight%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.ShowsNavigationUI%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.ShowsNavigationUI%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowHeight%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowWidth%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page.WindowTitle%2A>

trans-unit.source: - It has designer support in [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_visualstu](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-visualstu-md.md)].
trans-unit.target: -Det støtter designer [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_visualstu](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-visualstu-md.md)].

trans-unit.source: When a page is first navigated to, a new instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page> class is created.
trans-unit.target: Når en side først navigeres til en ny forekomst av den <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>klassen er opprettet.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>

trans-unit.source: When a page is navigated away from (either back or forward), an entry for the page is added to navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Når en side navigerer bort fra (tilbake eller fremover), lagt en oppføring for siden til navigasjon historikk.

trans-unit.source: By default, the entry does not reference the page object.
trans-unit.target: Som standard refererer ikke posten page-objekt.

trans-unit.source: Instead, the entry contains a pack [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] for the page.
trans-unit.target: I stedet posten inneholder en pakke [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] for siden.

trans-unit.source: When the entry for the page is navigated to using navigation history, the pack [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] is used to create a new instance of the page.
trans-unit.target: Når oppføringen for siden navigeres til ved hjelp av navigasjonslogg pakken [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] brukes til å opprette en ny forekomst av siden.

trans-unit.source: This behavior is the default, to avoid excessive memory use: retaining page instances can quickly consume memory, particularly those with a nontrivial amount of content.
trans-unit.target: Dette er standard, å unngå mye minnebruk: beholder siden forekomster kan bruke raskt minne, spesielt de med vanskelig å mengder innhold.

trans-unit.source: This problem is augmented by the fact that there is no limit to the number of entries that can be stored in the back and forward stacks of navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Dette problemet er maskinvareadministrasjonspakke av at det er ingen grense for antall oppføringer som kan lagres i tilbake og fremover bunker for navigasjon historikk.

trans-unit.source: In contrast, storing pack [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri#plural](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-urisharpplural-md.md)] for pages has virtually no impact on memory consumption.
trans-unit.target: Lagrer derimot pack [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri#plural](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-urisharpplural-md.md)] for sider er nesten ingen innvirkning på minneforbruk.

trans-unit.source: The main side effect of creating new instances of a page is that page state is not remembered from one instance of a page to another.
trans-unit.target: Den primære side oppretting av nye forekomster av en side virker at sidestatus ikke er lagret fra en forekomst av en side til en annen.

trans-unit.source: In these cases, [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-wpf-md.md)] offers several techniques for remembering state.
trans-unit.target: I slike tilfeller [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-wpf-md.md)] tilbyr flere metoder for å huske tilstand.

trans-unit.source: To keep a page alive, you set the KeepAlive property to `true` (the default is `false`).
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil beholde en side aktivt sett egenskapen KeepAlive til `true` (standard er `false`).

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Pages that are instantiated and navigated to using only code (for example, calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>), are automatically kept alive.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Sider som startes og navigeres til ved hjelp av bare koden (for eksempel kaller <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>), holdes automatisk aktive.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: You should avoid setting KeepAlive to `true` unless you need to: - When a page has a lot of content, it may take a long time to instantiate.

trans-unit.source: Gets the navigation service that the host of the page is using to manage navigation.
trans-unit.target: Henter tjenesten navigasjon verten for siden bruker til å behandle navigasjon.

trans-unit.source: Pages can be hosted by multiple types of hosts, including <xref:System.Windows.Window>, <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, and a browser.
trans-unit.target: Sider kan være vert flere typer verter, inkludert <xref:System.Windows.Window>, <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, og en nettleser.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Window>

trans-unit.source: Pages often need to integrate with their host's navigation to provide in-page navigation support.
trans-unit.target: Sider må ofte integrere med sine vert navigasjon å gi i-Sidenavigering støtte.

trans-unit.source: However, because a page may not know what its host will be at run time, it cannot integrate directly with its host's navigation members to do so.
trans-unit.target: Fordi en side ikke kan vet hva verten blir ved kjøretid, kan den imidlertid integrere direkte med den vert navigasjon medlemmer til å gjøre dette.

trans-unit.source: Instead, it can attempt to use a navigation service, which is a service that supports browser-style navigation and is encapsulated by the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> class.
trans-unit.target: I stedet prøver den å bruke en navigasjon-tjenesten, som er en tjeneste som støtter nettleseren-stil navigasjon og innkapslet av <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>klasse.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.source: You cannot create your own <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> instance, though.
trans-unit.target: Du kan ikke opprette din egen <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>serverforekomsten, men.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.source: Instead, host types such as <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, or a browser create their own <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> instance that you can access from the NavigationService property.
trans-unit.target: I stedet vert typer som <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, eller en nettleser lage sine egne <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>-forekomst som du har tilgang til fra egenskapen NavigationService.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: The navigation service that is returned from the NavigationService property is the instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> class that is managed by the first navigator up the visual tree.
trans-unit.target: Navigasjon tjenesten som er returnert fra egenskapen NavigationService er forekomsten av den <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>klasse som administreres av første navigatoren opp visual treet.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.source: If one is not found, `null` is returned, indicating a page's host does not support navigation.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det ikke finnes, `null` returneres som angir en side verten ikke støtter navigeringen.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page> in an [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xbap-md.md)] can only use WindowHeight to change the height of [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)]; the height cannot be changed by setting <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.MinHeight%2A>, or <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.MaxHeight%2A>.

trans-unit.source: The minimum height of the [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)] window is 150 pixels.
trans-unit.target: Minimumshøyden for den [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)] vinduet er 150 piksler.

trans-unit.source: For browser-hosted pages, this means that the value of WindowHeight may not be applied if it would cause the total height of the [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)] window to be less than 150 pixels.
trans-unit.target: Dette betyr at verdien for WindowHeight ikke kan brukes hvis den vil forårsake totalt høyden på for nettleseren vertsbaserte sider i [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)] vinduet for å være mindre enn 150 piksler.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the title of the host <xref href="System.Windows.Window"></xref> or <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow"></xref> of a <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Page"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir tittelen på verten <xref href="System.Windows.Window"> </xref> eller <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow"> </xref> av en <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Page"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: By default, the title of a window that hosts a page, including <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> and [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)], is the name of the file that is currently being hosted (with an .xaml extension if the page is loose [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)], or an .xbap extension if the page is part of an [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xbap-md.md)]).
trans-unit.target: Som standard tittelen på et vindu som er vert for en side, inkludert <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>og [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-iegeneric-md.md)], er navnet på filen som vert (med filtypen .xaml Hvis siden er miste [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)], eller filtypen .xbap Hvis siden er en del av en [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xbap-md.md)]).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: A page can change the default by setting its WindowTitle property.
trans-unit.target: En side kan endre standard ved å sette egenskapen WindowTitle.

trans-unit.source: Once a page sets the title of a window in this way, the window's title does not change until another page sets WindowTitle with a different value.
trans-unit.target: Når en side angir tittelen på et vindu på denne måten, endres ikke den vindustittel til en annen side angir WindowTitle med en annen verdi.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page> must be the topmost piece of content in a window for WindowTitle to have an effect; if a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page> is hosted within a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, for example, setting WindowTitle does not change the title of the host window.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > I <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>må være den øverste del av innholdet i et vindu for WindowTitle har en effekt; hvis en <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>ligger i en <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, for eksempel innstillingen WindowTitle endrer ikke tittelen på vinduet verten.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>
